# bastion DNS never-sink allowlist — the DNS-path counterpart to policy.allowlist (the IP path).
# Domains here are NEVER sinkholed, no matter what a blocklist says. A poisoned or over-aggressive
# list could otherwise NXDOMAIN the box's own update path, its liveness deps, or your critical
# services box-wide. One domain per line; an entry covers that domain AND all its subdomains.
# edge-dnsblock-update ALSO auto-protects the configured egress-probe host and DNS upstream at
# runtime, so those survive even if this file is emptied. Operator additions come from
# machine.conf [monitoring] dns_allowlist (rendered onto the last line). DO NOT add a real
# installation-specific value here in the committed template.

# The blocklists themselves are fetched from GitHub — sinkholing this would brick all future updates.
github.com
githubusercontent.com
# AI backend API (the default egress probe) + the secondary egress canary.
anthropic.com
cloudflare.com
# Distro update infrastructure — sinkholing these breaks pacman / apt / dnf.
archlinux.org
debian.org
ubuntu.com
fedoraproject.org
# Time sync.
ntp.org
pool.ntp.org

